benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/healthcheck - Put the host out of rotation

covered: Valid Deletion: TC01 (successful delete) and TC12 (regression) cover successful host removal and post-deletion verification
Concurrency: TC11 covers concurrent DELETE requests and race-condition handling
Authorization: TC02 and TC03 verify 401 responses for missing/invalid authentication
Endpoint/Server Error Handling: TC05 (503) service unavailable and TC06 (500) internal error
Method Not Allowed: TC07 validates 405 for an invalid HTTP method
Invalid Input/Headers: TC09 (malicious payload) and TC13 (malicious headers) return 400 (or 401 for headers) indicating invalid input/auth
Extra Parameters: TC08 demonstrates that extra query parameters are tolerated and still return 204
Performance: TC10 (normal load) and TC11 (concurrent load) cover response time expectations under load
Edge Case: TC14 covers system with no hosts in rotation (409) as a non-rotatable resource scenario
Regression Coverage: TC12 confirms host status can be queried after deletion
gaps: Soft Deletes: No tests covering soft-delete semantics (if applicable to domain) or audit trail
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or rate-limit behaviors on DELETE requests
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE/healthcheck
Explicit Non-Existent Resource: No dedicated test for 404 Not Found semantics on delete (beyond no-rotation edge), or explicit resource-not-found flow
Parameter Validation Depth: Limited coverage of invalid/edge parameter combinations beyond extra parameters (e.g., malformed query params beyond TC08)
recommendations: Add a soft-delete semantics test if the domain expects soft deletion or audit trails
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate 429 or equivalent behavior under burst DELETE requests
Add caching header validation tests (ETag/Cache-Control) for 204 responses
Include an explicit 404 Not Found scenario for non-rotation/non-existent resource, to clarify resource-not-found semantics
Expand parameter validation with additional invalid combinations (e.g., invalid types for query/body parameters) to strengthen input validation
